<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Leafweir</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-01-17 14:55:46</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Breaking the king requires 6 people for safety, but I have<BR>
done it with 5. You need a 40+ SK/Monk, a 45+ enchanter,<BR>
a 40+ bard, a 45+ cleric, and a 45+ Mage/Necro. One you<BR>
have taken the pool room (and the HUGE water elemental),<BR>
have everyone step back into the hallway. The monk/SK pulls<BR>
a gang of mobs into the back end of the pool room and<BR>
feigns death. Once all mobs leave but one someone (the bard<BR>
perhaps) pulls if off him and the group kills it. Should<BR>
feign death fail to work, the puller should allow<BR>
him/herself to die. Getting 1 resurrection is quicker<BR>
than doing 5. The puller should not stand up until the<BR>
group is ready for another mob, otherwise you risk fighting<BR>
far more than you want to. Once the outer section is clear<BR>
(ignore the herbalist for now) proceed to do the same with<BR>
the 5 spawns in the king room. THe group can move up to just<BR>
past the curtain at this poitn and I prefer to feign at the<BR>
last corner before the ladder to the herbalist. Done<BR>
poperly a group of 5 can break this and a group of 4 can<BR>
hold the king room spawns. (I would maintain 5 if you want<BR>
to continue pulling the area.)<BR>
<BR>
Break down of jobs<BR>
Enchanter - crowd control should you need it and clarity.<BR>
Augmentation or Alacrity is nice on the tanks too.<BR>
<BR>
SK/Monk - Feign puller. I prefer an SK simply because I am<BR>
one. If you are an SK make sure clinging darkness is your<BR>
pull spell. Use cling not engulf because you won't be able<BR>
to med once you start.<BR>
<BR>
Cleric - Heal/Symbol/Resolution - Oh yeah, stun the king<BR>
silly, he likes to heal.<BR>
<BR>
Bard - back up tank. mana singer.<BR>
<BR>
Necro/Mage - Pets are a nice 3rd tank, do good damage. And<BR>
each of these has some nice offensive spells.<BR>
<BR>
Remember, feigners never EVER get up until yer ready for<BR>
a new pull (the few times I did get up to help at the<BR>
party's request were horrific). Crowd control is a must.<BR>
Only fight one mob at a time. Use mana song and clarity<BR>
to cut your down times. <BR>
<BR>
If you have a 6th, a druid for plast and the extra nuking<BR>
and back up healing is nice. but really, anything would fill<BR>
the 6th slot nicely. Rule of thumb, caster sshould be 45+<BR>
and meleers 40+.<BR>
<BR>
Good luck,<BR>
<BR>
Leafweir<BR>
42nd lvl Shadow Knight<BR>
Fennin Ro<BR>
Send replies to leifweir@aol.com<BR>
(the email addy does have an intentional i instead of a)<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
